[SN]TITLE[SN]
Evian Championship: In Gee Chun leads by four shots as record beckons

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
South Korea's In Gee Chun established a four-shot lead after the third round of the Evian Championship to remain on course for her second career major.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 22-year-old, who won the 2015 US Open, shot a six-under-par 65 to pull clear of compatriot Sung Hyun Park, who signed for a 67.
Chun had six birdies and an eagle for the round, her only blot a double bogey on the ninth hole.
At 19 under, she could now record the lowest ever 72-hole score at a major.
